Sentencas: For solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) to succeed as a next-generation, clean energy conversion device, they must be made to run more efficiently at low temperatures <500 degrees C. To improve electrode kinetics at these lower temperatures, we investigate using atomic layer deposition (ALD) to fabricate mixed electronic-ionic conducting electrodes of (LaxSr1-x)MnO3 (LSM).
Titulo: Atomic layer deposition of LSM cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Lanthanum oxide was grown from La(Me4Cp)(3) and water with a source temperature of 220 degrees C with a stoichiometry of La2O3.
Titulo: Atomic layer deposition of LSM cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Strontium oxide was grown from Sr(n-PrMe4Cp)(2) and water with a precursor sublimation temperature of 210 degrees C and a stoichiometry of SrO, with little carbon contamination.
Titulo: Atomic layer deposition of LSM cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Manganese oxide was grown from Mn(Me4Cp)(2) at a source temperature of 180 degrees C and water as oxidant; the stoichiometry was confirmed to be MnO2.
Titulo: Atomic layer deposition of LSM cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: La/H2O/La/H2O/Mn/H2O/Sr/H2O/Mn/H2O/La/H2O/La/H2O. LSM was crystalline as deposited when grown on crystalline yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) substrates.
Titulo: Atomic layer deposition of LSM cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: On fuel cells with LSM as the 95 nm thick, dense cathode, 100 nm thick, dense YSZ as electrolyte, and porous 80 nm thick Pt anode, a peak power density of 0.2 mu W/cm(2) was achieved at 450 degrees C. Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy shows that low oxygen diffusivity in LSM and slow kinetics of the oxygen reduction reaction on LSM were the limiting resistances in the fuel cell, suggesting that LSM is not an optimal low temperature cathode.
Titulo: Atomic layer deposition of LSM cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells
